It&#39;s opinion, but I don&#39;t agree with your choices.  

 1. &quot;Service&quot; - too generic, not necessarily about data.  Those usually mean SOAP or, better yet, REST, to me.
 2. The query object?  I think it&#39;s a better contract to spell out what the user should pass.  Don&#39;t worry about being flexible; prefer being clear.
 3. I&#39;d expect the return value from getUser to be a User.

Here&#39;s what I&#39;d do:

    public interface UserRepository {  
        List&lt;User&gt; find();
        User find(Integer id);
        List&lt;User&gt; find(String lastName);
        Integer save(User user);
        void update(User user);
        void delete(Integer id);
    }

