answers.body_markdown:
You can use [`Coroutine`][1] to do a heavy task and avoid freezing.

Change your method return type to `IEnumerator`

    IEnumerator Heavy() 
    {
        // some real heavy task
        for (int i = 1; i &lt; 10000000; i++) 
        {
            balh();
            yield return new WaitForEndOfFrame();
        }
    }

And simply call it like this:

    StartCoroutine(Heavy());

You just have to run it on a `MonoBehaviour`. that&#39;s it.

  [1]: https://docs.unity3d.com/Manual/Coroutines.html

